I'm pretty sure no one here was saying the type of ship Boba Fett flies is a "Slave 1." It's pretty well understood that _Slave I_ is just the ship's name. Like the YT-1300 freighter Han Solo flies is named the _Millennium Falcon,_ and Princess Leia's CR90 corvette is named _Tantive IV._

@MisterPCS2 how would have adapt them though?  They're set 5 years after RotJ, so live action is out unless you think folk would be fine with re-casting all the iconic roles.  Maybe with AI advancing it might be possible one day, but it certainly wasn't an option when Disney first started making movies.

Personally I have no interesting in adapting Star Wars books or comics into movies.  I know the stories already.  Star Wars started life on film.  If I go to see a Star Wars movies I want it to be a fresh, original story where I don't know what's going to happen.  You could never have an "Empire moment" with an adaptation.

Of course that doesn't excuse crap movies like those Disney have churned out.

